11:13.324 --> 11:16.066
But maybe we're not
understanding.

11:16.110 --> 11:18.199
Okay?
If Toni was white,

11:18.242 --> 11:20.331
you'd still love the story,
right?

11:20.375 --> 11:22.072
Right, but if Toni was white,
she wouldn't be in prison.

11:22.116 --> 11:24.727
-Fair point.
-Sorry, Beth.

11:24.771 --> 11:26.598
-I don't like the optics.
-The optics?

11:26.642 --> 11:28.644
Since when does Fiona
have to be a wizard

11:28.688 --> 11:30.690
-to write about wizards?
-Dude, what the fuck?

11:30.733 --> 11:32.692
-Sorry.
-Please tell me you didn't just

11:32.735 --> 11:34.432
equate America's original sin

11:34.476 --> 11:35.956
with Ron Weasley.

11:35.999 --> 11:37.653
Okay, I'm sorry, you guys.

11:37.697 --> 11:38.915
I've been doing this
a lot longer than all of you,

11:38.959 --> 11:42.136
and this is
a huge opportunity.

11:42.179 --> 11:45.269
I just feel like, when do we
ever get to write a story

11:45.313 --> 11:48.185
that's great
and also redeems a human life?

11:48.229 --> 11:51.145
But that's-that's why
we signed up for the job.

11:51.188 --> 11:53.495
Or at least it's why I did.

11:55.149 --> 11:57.499
Fine, but please,

11:57.542 --> 11:59.631
God, keep it short for once.

11:59.675 --> 12:00.763
Oh, thank you.

12:00.807 --> 12:02.243
Mwah! I love you.

12:02.286 --> 12:04.201
-[coworkers murmur]
-Never do that again.

12:04.245 --> 12:05.725
Okay.

12:08.466 --> 12:10.947
-Hey, you owe me.
-I'm sorry. I do. I owe you.

12:10.991 --> 12:13.080
♪

12:23.830 --> 12:25.309
Hi there.

12:25.353 --> 12:27.137
Beth Burgess
to see Toni Plimpton.

12:27.181 --> 12:28.835
Are you a lawyer?

12:28.878 --> 12:31.011
No.

12:31.054 --> 12:32.969
No visits on Thursdays
unless you're a lawyer.

12:33.013 --> 12:34.928
Okay, well, I'm a,
I'm a journalist.

12:34.971 --> 12:37.017
And I'm working
on Ms. Plimpton's case,

12:37.060 --> 12:39.323
so in a way I-I'm like a lawyer.

12:39.367 --> 12:41.282
She's not a lawyer.

12:41.325 --> 12:43.327
Not a lawyer exactly.

12:43.371 --> 12:44.764
No. Look, I need to see

12:44.807 --> 12:46.417
-Toni Plimpton.
-No.

12:46.461 --> 12:49.812
I don't think you understand
the stakes here.

12:49.856 --> 12:51.161
That woman is innocent.

12:51.205 --> 12:52.815
Do you understand Thursday?

12:52.859 --> 12:54.904
No visits on Thursday.

12:54.948 --> 12:56.993
Okay, uh...

12:57.037 --> 12:58.429
Could-could I call her?

12:58.473 --> 12:59.822
Or-or could you have her
call me?

12:59.866 --> 13:01.302
That's my card.

13:02.172 --> 13:04.784
Lady, do you get
how a prison works?

13:04.827 --> 13:07.395
BETH:
I know she has rights.

13:07.438 --> 13:10.137
Uh, this has to be
a violation of her rights.

13:10.180 --> 13:11.529
-That's really funny.
-[guard laughs]

13:11.573 --> 13:14.141
Oh, man.
Can you say that again,

13:14.184 --> 13:15.969
just the way you said it?

13:16.012 --> 13:17.884
I want to remember it
to tell it to the guys.

13:17.927 --> 13:20.669
Okay. Go ahead.
Mock me, threaten me.

13:20.712 --> 13:24.064
I'm not leaving
until I see Toni Plimpton, okay?

13:24.107 --> 13:25.239
This is a protest.

13:25.282 --> 13:27.284
So, until you let me in,

13:27.328 --> 13:30.897
I'm-a stay right here,
raising hell!

13:31.898 --> 13:34.596
ANCHORMAN [on TV]: The body
was found in the area east...

13:34.639 --> 13:36.206
[phone chimes, vibrates]

13:36.250 --> 13:37.729
Cause of death appears

13:37.773 --> 13:39.253
-to be strangulation.
-[sighs]: Shit.

13:39.296 --> 13:41.211
No suspects have been
arrested yet.

13:41.255 --> 13:43.518
TESSA: And that'll be Denver's
seventh homicide this year.

13:43.561 --> 13:45.825
Tragic stuff.

13:45.868 --> 13:49.524
But... on a lighter note,
uh, tonight

13:49.567 --> 13:51.395
I will be accepting my first

13:51.439 --> 13:54.007
Colorado Journalist
Association award,

13:54.050 --> 13:57.532
and I am just so beyond humbled.

13:57.575 --> 14:00.796
And I vow, I vow
to continue bringing you

14:00.840 --> 14:02.624
the stories
that matter most.

14:02.667 --> 14:04.844
De mi corazón a tuya,

14:04.887 --> 14:06.628
as my father used to say,
in heaven.

14:06.671 --> 14:08.673
"From my heart...
[kiss]

14:08.717 --> 14:11.285
to yours."

14:11.328 --> 14:13.722
ANCHORMAN: Thank you for that,
Tessa. In other news...

14:13.765 --> 14:15.680
Hello again.

14:15.724 --> 14:17.682
Do you happen to know if, uh,

14:17.726 --> 14:21.512
any other journalists
have come by to visit?

14:21.556 --> 14:24.472
Tessa Flores? She's...

14:24.515 --> 14:28.476
she's TV-pretty but in person
her head is way too big.

14:30.130 --> 14:31.392
[Beth sighs]

14:34.003 --> 14:36.005
Um...

14:36.049 --> 14:38.312
Have you heard
of Susan Burgess?

14:38.355 --> 14:41.924
She wrote a best-selling memoir
called Acts of Devotion,

14:41.968 --> 14:43.926
about a single mom
in the '80s.

14:43.970 --> 14:47.147
Kind of reinvented our concept
of modern motherhood.

14:47.190 --> 14:48.931
[sighs]

14:48.975 --> 14:51.151
Well, I'm her daughter.

14:53.283 --> 14:56.417
[quietly]:
Not a big reader? Okay.

15:02.945 --> 15:04.686
Five minutes.

15:06.079 --> 15:08.168
♪

15:10.779 --> 15:12.346
Get off me!

15:12.389 --> 15:15.697
I'm a taxpaying citizen!
I have the right to be here!

15:15.740 --> 15:18.308
-[Beth groans]
-OFFICER: Don't come back!

15:20.049 --> 15:22.530
I want my 20 bucks back!

15:24.358 --> 15:26.447
[busy chatter]

15:30.146 --> 15:31.974
You guys,
I'm so sorry I'm late.

15:32.018 --> 15:33.410
My boss is a total lunatic.

15:33.454 --> 15:35.586
-Hi.
-Hey.

15:35.630 --> 15:37.719
-What, still no table?
-No, they wouldn't seat us

15:37.762 --> 15:39.416
till our whole party's here.

15:39.460 --> 15:40.852
-Geez.
-Yeah.

15:40.896 --> 15:42.115
Why didn't you tell them
I was in the bathroom?

15:42.158 --> 15:43.290
Well, 'cause you weren't
in the bathroom.

15:43.333 --> 15:45.727
Okay, here, Beth.
Before I forget,

15:45.770 --> 15:47.555
I made you some prints
from the other day.

15:47.598 --> 15:49.992
-Oh, wow. Thanks.
-Yeah.

15:50.036 --> 15:53.213
BETH:
Aw, look at Ellie's little face.

15:53.256 --> 15:55.998
It's crazy how much she looks
like the both of you.

15:56.042 --> 15:57.652
So, what's this Marco tells us,

15:57.695 --> 16:00.481
-you're moving to Wyoming?
-[mutters]

16:00.524 --> 16:02.396
Wyoming is where white people
go to get killed in the woods.

16:02.439 --> 16:03.527
-Yeah, a-all right.
-Yeah, we're not moving

16:03.571 --> 16:05.007
to Wyoming. Right, babe?

16:05.051 --> 16:06.574
Well, I mean,
anything's possible.

16:06.617 --> 16:07.923
-It's not possible.
-They just posted the job today.

16:07.967 --> 16:09.403
It's possible.

16:09.446 --> 16:11.100
-Would you work out there?
-MARCO: Of course.

16:11.144 --> 16:13.842
No. No. That's why we're not
seriously considering it.

16:13.885 --> 16:15.017
-MARCO: Yes.
-Besides, I think I just landed

16:15.061 --> 16:17.411
a really big new story, so...

16:17.454 --> 16:19.413
-Oh, that's great!
-Yeah.

16:19.456 --> 16:21.154
Wait, hon.

16:21.197 --> 16:22.807
For real this time?

16:22.851 --> 16:24.853
-What? Yes, for real this time.
-[Wes shushing]

16:24.896 --> 16:26.246
She's coming back.

16:26.289 --> 16:28.030
MARCO: Excuse me, miss,
we're all here.

16:28.074 --> 16:31.164
-Great. Right this way.
-[phone vibrating]

16:31.207 --> 16:33.079
All right!

16:34.689 --> 16:36.299
Oh, uh, you guys.

16:36.343 --> 16:37.518
This is gonna take one second.

16:37.561 --> 16:38.998
-No, Beth. No, no, Beth.
-One second.

16:39.041 --> 16:40.042
-One second.
-Beth. Beth, Beth, Beth.

16:40.086 --> 16:41.478
No, no, no. I'm so hungry.

16:43.132 --> 16:44.220
[door closes]

16:44.264 --> 16:46.657
She just went to the bathroom.

16:46.701 --> 16:48.268
AUTOMATED VOICE: ...may be
recorded and monitored.

16:48.311 --> 16:50.922
To accept this call,
press one or say yes.

16:50.966 --> 16:52.533
-Yes!
-Now.

16:52.576 --> 16:54.056
Yes, yes, yes.

16:54.100 --> 16:56.015
[phone line beeps]

16:56.058 --> 16:59.192
Hey, Toni. Are you there?

16:59.235 --> 17:00.802
TONI: Hey, what the hell
do you think you're doing?

17:00.845 --> 17:02.543
Staging a protest or something?

17:02.586 --> 17:04.327
Yeah, I sure am.

17:04.371 --> 17:06.764
I told them I won't leave
until they let us talk.

17:06.808 --> 17:08.418
You fucking fascists!

17:08.462 --> 17:09.550
I hope you eat your own shit!

17:09.593 --> 17:11.160
-Hey, look.
-Sorry, not you.

17:11.204 --> 17:13.032
COs are up my ass right now.

17:13.075 --> 17:15.208
If you want to help me,
leave me the hell alone.

17:15.251 --> 17:16.992
Toni, listen.

17:17.036 --> 17:18.950
I know the first time
we met was...

17:18.994 --> 17:21.431
was weird, and-and
I'm really sorry about that,

17:21.475 --> 17:22.563
but I...

17:22.606 --> 17:24.608
I've been diving into your case

17:24.652 --> 17:27.785
and, uh, and doing
my homework and...

17:27.829 --> 17:30.353
Listen,
I went to your house.

17:30.397 --> 17:33.008
-My house?
-Yeah.

17:33.052 --> 17:35.619
I met Wyatt,
and-and-and he told me a lot.

17:35.663 --> 17:38.231
I mean, Mile-High Linens?

17:38.274 --> 17:39.493
Yeah, it's a front.

17:39.536 --> 17:40.711
Yeah, obviously.

17:40.755 --> 17:42.365
And-and I found
a bunch of guns,

17:42.409 --> 17:44.411
clearly illegal guns.

17:44.454 --> 17:46.108
Yeah, he's a gun runner,
I told you.

17:46.152 --> 17:48.067
No, I know,
I know that you did.

17:48.110 --> 17:49.633
And I just...

17:49.677 --> 17:51.766
I just wanted to say
that I believe you.

17:51.809 --> 17:55.378
And your story,
I know how to tell it.

17:55.422 --> 17:58.860
Like, I know how to write it
so that you come off innocent.

17:58.903 --> 18:00.383
I aminnocent.

18:00.427 --> 18:01.776
Yes, but the-the world
doesn't know that.

18:01.819 --> 18:04.300
-Beth.
-Listen, I can do this.

18:04.344 --> 18:05.519
I know I can. [stammers]

18:05.562 --> 18:06.607
I really can do this.

18:06.650 --> 18:09.740
Beth, I gave the story to Tessa.

18:09.784 --> 18:11.220
[quietly]:
Fuck.

18:11.264 --> 18:13.962
I mean, she has
a bigger audience.

18:14.005 --> 18:15.616
[scoffs]

18:15.659 --> 18:17.531
How is a local
Denver news station

18:17.574 --> 18:20.055
a bigger audience
than the World Wide Web?

18:20.099 --> 18:22.884
And she has, uh,
more credibility.

18:22.927 --> 18:24.625
What did she tell you?

18:24.668 --> 18:26.105
That you got fired
from theChronicle

18:26.148 --> 18:28.933
'cause you misquoted people.

18:28.977 --> 18:31.153
-Put words in their mouths.
-No.

18:31.197 --> 18:33.068
Those were false allegations

18:33.112 --> 18:34.852
made by a lying scumbag.

18:34.896 --> 18:37.290
I was railroaded, okay?

18:37.333 --> 18:39.379
You of all people
should understand that.

18:39.422 --> 18:42.208
Toni, please.

18:42.251 --> 18:43.905
You're making the wrong choice.

18:43.948 --> 18:46.125
I know Tessa Flores.
She's vile.

18:46.168 --> 18:48.257
Yeah, but we watch her in here
every night.

18:48.301 --> 18:50.520
And when she speaks,
people listen.

18:50.564 --> 18:52.479
They believe.

18:54.742 --> 18:56.613
I just want to get back
with my baby girl,

18:56.657 --> 18:59.181
and Tessa is my best chance.

19:00.182 --> 19:02.141
So, that's it?

19:02.184 --> 19:03.968
Look, if you ever get
that tattoo,

19:04.012 --> 19:05.535
you let me know, all right?

19:05.579 --> 19:07.102
[line beeps, clicks]

19:07.146 --> 19:08.190
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Your call has ended.

19:08.234 --> 19:10.627
-Goodbye.
-[sighs]

19:11.976 --> 19:14.022
[sobs quietly]

19:35.261 --> 19:37.132
I stole these from a table.

19:37.176 --> 19:39.961
-Uh, they look untouched.
-Oh, thank you, Marco.

19:40.004 --> 19:41.180
[knocking on window]

19:41.223 --> 19:43.182
Work emergency!

19:43.225 --> 19:45.314
Sorry!

19:47.142 --> 19:49.057
Hi, excuse me.

19:49.100 --> 19:51.364
We'll just take a table
for three.

19:55.933 --> 19:59.241
TESSA: But in a country
where the press is

19:59.285 --> 20:01.504
under assault...

20:01.548 --> 20:05.116
and where media is no longer
synonymous with objectivity

20:05.160 --> 20:07.728
but instead with bias,

20:07.771 --> 20:10.557
we, all of us here
in this room,

20:10.600 --> 20:13.037
are this nation's last line
of defense

20:13.081 --> 20:16.780
against outrageous
manipulations of the truth.

20:16.824 --> 20:19.914
This award is
for all of you out there

20:19.957 --> 20:23.222
on the front lines,
speaking truth to power.

20:23.265 --> 20:26.834
Just know that I see you.

20:26.877 --> 20:30.446
I see you.

20:30.490 --> 20:32.709
Te veo.

20:32.753 --> 20:35.321
-[applause]
-Thank you.

20:41.283 --> 20:43.764
Hi, can I get a...

20:43.807 --> 20:46.070
Hello?

20:46.114 --> 20:48.334
Nice. Real nice.

20:48.377 --> 20:52.207
What are you doing here?

20:52.251 --> 20:55.689
Getting a drink.

20:55.732 --> 20:59.606
Tessa Flores taking home
the blue ribbon.

20:59.649 --> 21:01.129
How far we've fallen.

21:01.172 --> 21:03.262
Oh, well,
some of us didn't fall.

21:03.305 --> 21:05.307
-We were pushed.
-Don't.

21:05.351 --> 21:07.570
-Don't dredge it all back up.
-Just admit it.

21:07.614 --> 21:09.572
-I want my fish back.
-Why?

21:09.616 --> 21:11.226
So you can flush it
down the toilet

21:11.270 --> 21:13.576
as soon as it doesn't do
exactly what you want?

21:13.620 --> 21:15.752
I want my reputation back,
Ravi.

21:15.796 --> 21:17.711
I don't suppose you have that
sitting in a glass tank

21:17.754 --> 21:19.800
in your office?

21:19.843 --> 21:22.368
It's a tropical red swordtail,
Beth.

21:22.411 --> 21:24.544
It needs very specific food.

21:24.587 --> 21:26.981
I didn't take your fish.

21:28.199 --> 21:30.332
[sighs] Look, there's
an exotic pet store

21:30.376 --> 21:33.335
down on 26th and Cherry.
Ask for Pete.

21:35.946 --> 21:40.081
And remember, you're mad at me,
not the fish.

21:43.389 --> 21:46.261
Can I get a goddamn drink?!

21:46.305 --> 21:48.089
Please?

21:54.922 --> 21:58.055
TESSA:
Well, look at you, all...

21:58.099 --> 22:01.189
dolled up on my big night.

22:05.149 --> 22:07.761
Is this because of Toni?

22:07.804 --> 22:09.806
It's not my fault
she has brains in her head.

22:09.850 --> 22:11.852
You're just using her.

22:11.895 --> 22:14.855
I'm using her?
I'm using her, wow.

22:14.898 --> 22:16.683
What are you trying to do?
You're trying to...

22:16.726 --> 22:18.728
save her precious soul?

22:18.772 --> 22:21.383
She's not just
another piece of crime-porn

22:21.427 --> 22:22.906
to feed to
your perverted fanbase.

22:22.950 --> 22:25.561
Do not tell me
how to do my job.

22:25.605 --> 22:27.694
-You've had plenty of chances.
-Okay.

22:27.737 --> 22:30.871
-Okay?
-Fine. Fine.

22:30.914 --> 22:34.048
Just, please look
into Wyatt and the linens.

22:34.091 --> 22:35.919
Okay? There's more there.

22:35.963 --> 22:39.096
It could be a path
to reopening her case.

22:39.140 --> 22:41.490
Thank you, but I'd really
rather just skip

22:41.534 --> 22:45.842
the Beth Burgess master class
for now.

22:45.886 --> 22:48.367
Why don't you, uh, watch this
while I take a piss.

22:48.410 --> 22:51.761
Get reacquainted
with an old friend.

22:54.111 --> 22:56.244
[award clatters on ground]

22:57.158 --> 22:59.508
["Everytime You Go Away"
by Paul Young playing]

23:04.295 --> 23:06.472
-[song continues on radio]
-[sobbing quietly]

23:10.258 --> 23:15.394
♪ Hey, if we can solve
any problem♪

23:15.437 --> 23:18.092
[car behind revving]

23:18.135 --> 23:20.007
♪ Then why do we lose
so many tears?♪

23:20.050 --> 23:21.704
[blinker ticking]

23:21.748 --> 23:23.793
[revving]

23:23.837 --> 23:28.015
♪ Oh, so you go again♪

23:29.103 --> 23:34.151
♪ When the leading man appears♪

23:35.109 --> 23:39.853
♪ Always the same thing♪

23:39.896 --> 23:41.985
♪ Can't you see♪

23:42.029 --> 23:44.118
-[tires screeching]
-♪ We've got everything♪

23:44.161 --> 23:46.816
♪ Going on and on and on♪

23:46.860 --> 23:50.994
♪ Every time you go away♪

23:52.561 --> 23:55.477
♪ You take a piece of me
with you...♪

23:55.521 --> 23:57.087
[tires screech]

23:57.131 --> 23:58.262
EMPLOYEE [distorted]:
Uh, welcome to...

23:58.306 --> 23:59.438
What can I get you?

23:59.481 --> 24:00.569
Can you call 911?

24:00.613 --> 24:02.484
There's a creep following me.

24:02.528 --> 24:04.443
[distorted chatter]

24:04.486 --> 24:06.227
Any-Anything else?

24:06.270 --> 24:07.489
Excuse me, ma'am,

24:07.533 --> 24:08.795
-anything else?
-No.

24:08.838 --> 24:09.970
Fuck this.

24:16.716 --> 24:19.283
Hey! Hey!

24:19.327 --> 24:21.851
-Goddamn it.
-Look at my fucking car!

24:21.895 --> 24:24.811
What the fuck are you doing?!

24:25.768 --> 24:28.336
What the fuck are youdoing?!

24:28.379 --> 24:30.120
You followed me.

24:30.164 --> 24:31.513
You tracked me down

24:31.557 --> 24:32.514
-and you followed me?
-Shut up, shut up.

24:32.558 --> 24:33.994
Well, guess what, George,

24:34.037 --> 24:34.516
you picked a real shit time
to follow me.

24:34.560 --> 24:36.257
Shut up.

24:36.300 --> 24:38.477
If you need a witness,
I saw the whole thing.

24:38.520 --> 24:39.695
She's clearly nuts.

24:39.739 --> 24:41.305
That's okay.
It's under control.

24:41.349 --> 24:43.090
Thank you, sir. I'm not nuts.
He's a criminal.

24:43.133 --> 24:44.178
-Call the police!
-I said...

24:44.221 --> 24:45.788
Shut the fuck up!

24:45.832 --> 24:47.442
You really know how
to pick 'em, don't you, George?

24:47.486 --> 24:48.878
What was it about me
that made you go,

24:48.922 --> 24:50.576
"Oh, I know,
I'll give her a hard time?"

24:50.619 --> 24:52.360
-What was it?
-Lady,

24:52.403 --> 24:54.275
-keep your fucking voice down.
-How pathetic do I look?

24:54.318 --> 24:56.059
-I get it! You made your point!
-Oh, my God. Shut the fuck up.

24:56.103 --> 25:00.281
I'm a husk! I'm a dried-up husk
of a useless woman!

25:00.324 --> 25:01.717
You better calm

25:01.761 --> 25:03.153
-the fuck down, lady.
-Why?

25:03.197 --> 25:04.590
-[shushes]
-Why?

25:04.633 --> 25:06.026
So I can spend my life
pumping out babies,

25:06.069 --> 25:08.507
writing wizard stories
in the Tetons?

25:08.550 --> 25:11.422
You go ahead and kill me.
